                            <comment id="17833868" author="jensgr@gmx.net" created="Thu, 4 Apr 2024 08:32:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We also see timeouts after upgrading to 4.0,4 where 4.0.3 works fine (not using HTTP2).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17834650" author="JIRAUSER304811" created="Sun, 7 Apr 2024 10:03:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah looks like the finalizer (as well as other potentially related code) was introduced here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cxf/commit/5ffdb906b560458ad8df5a892554b6e806d98d9e#diff-660ab7b7b6a7b75d899f2a1cd889b168aadd5a194d2aa9fbae875c1b56891c6c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;Change from using aonymous inner classes to static classes to avoid h&#8230; &#183; apache/cxf@5ffdb90 (github.com)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Better to avoid using 4.0.4 for the time being I guess&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17926556" author="paulbors" created="Wed, 12 Feb 2025 19:28:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is caused by a shallow copy of the ClientConfiguration inside the WebClient.fromClient() method that in turn calls&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
WebClient.copyProperties() and copies reference which are later set to NULL:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;newClient.setConfiguration(oldClient.getConfiguration());&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
If we change that to a deep copy, this issue goes away. Why? Because WebClient IS-A AbstractClient and when the original WebClient you copied is destroyed by the GC and the AbstractClient.finalize() is invoked... it calls AbstractClient.close() which in turn does a nice&#160;&lt;br/&gt;
cfg = null;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now your in-flight WebClient as copied from the original one points to a NULL ClientConfiguration so... IO Exception.&lt;br/&gt;
&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17931677" author="reta" created="Sat, 1 Mar 2025 16:15:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix introduces ClientConfiguration referencing (since implementing the deep copy of it is quite difficult), the new bus property `&lt;font color=&quot;#000000&quot;&gt;use.configuration.reference.when.copy&lt;/font&gt;` (&lt;b&gt;true&lt;/b&gt; by default) allows to circumvent the referencing mechanism by falling back to sharing the configuration (leading to this issue).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
